CAPSTONE ASSIGNMENT

1. Open Cisco Packet Tracer and place 2 routers, 2 switches, and 4 PCs.
2. Connect PCs to switches and switches to routers using copper straight-through cables.
3. Connect both routers using a **Serial DCE (WAN) cable**.
4. Assign IP addresses to router LAN and WAN interfaces.
5. Enable interfaces using `no shutdown` command.
6. Configure a DHCP server on LAN 1 to assign IPs automatically.
7. Set all PCs to DHCP mode.
8. Configure **RIPv2 routing** on both routers.
9. Verify routing tables using `show ip route`.
10. Test connectivity by pinging from LAN 1 PC to LAN 2 PC.
